@D88nielC I swear to God I never heard anyone saying Henry Cavill is terrible actor. He is amazing actor. Fans absolutely love his work. 

Versatility and Range: Cavill has demonstrated the ability to move from intense period dramas and fantasy to modern blockbusters and spy thrillers, showing a broad acting spectrum. Commitment to Roles: He is known for fully immersing himself in characters and finding their emotional core, even in roles that are physically demanding. Strong Performances: Many critics and fans point to his performances in The Tudors, Man of Steel, and Mission: Impossible – Fallout as examples of his skill. Knowledge of Source Material: He is respected for his deep understanding and passion for the projects he takes on, such as the Witcher games, and advocates for quality within the industry.

